acpi: thermal: retain downstream hwmon, power and sensor fixes

Preserve each ACPI thermal zone's bus ID as its thermal-core type.  Use an
independent "acpitz" hwmon type to group the labelled readings under one
adapter.  This keeps unique types available to thermal APIs, sysfs,
netlink, and tracing without sacrificing readable sensors output.

Treat SSTP as an optional power-allocation hint.  Keep SWIT as the
power_allocator activation threshold instead of publishing it as a
second passive trip consumed by step_wise.  Select power_allocator only
for zones with a valid SWIT range.  Map the CIX OPP-sized processor
cooling states to their corresponding CPPC frequencies instead of
applying the legacy 20% reduction repeatedly.

Make the optional SPRG and DPRG power lookups return zero deterministically
when firmware omits them.  Reject affinity index 12 as out of range for the
twelve Sky1 CPUs.

